# Match highlight overlays

Fuzzy match highlighting should overlay the styles already used by each part of
a session row. This case matches characters in the live session name, the dim
repo parent path, and the plain repo basename; the linked SVG snapshot preserves
those combined styles.

    :bins jj cat mkdir

> [!NOTE]
> 'jj', 'cat', and 'mkdir' are available.

    :copy tests/fixtures/jjconfig.toml .jjconfig.toml (copied)

    :t rename-session -t 0 runner (success)
    :$ mkdir code (exit: 0)
    :$ jj git init code/blue (exit: 0)
    :$ jj describe -R code/blue -m "blue commit" (exit: 0)
    :t new-session -d -s tone~one "cat" (success)
    :t set-option -t tone~one @sesh.repo code/blue (success)
    :t new-session -d -s ui "sesh" (success)
    :t resize-window -t ui:0 -x 100 -y 10 (success)
    :pane ui:0.0
    :settle (settled)

Hide the preview so the color snapshot focuses on the list row. The query
`onecb` crosses the live session name (`one`), compact repo parent (`c`), and
basename (`b`) spans.

    :k C-p
    :settle (settled)
    :k onecb
    :snap --color

```terminal
session: onecb                                                                                     ┃
  1/3 | [C-r] repo: none | [C-x] close, [C-f] flag                                                 ┃
▌⬤ tone~one                                 c/blue                                                 ┃
                                                                                                   ┃
                                                                                                   ┃
                                                                                                   ┃
                                                                                                   ┃
                                                                                                   ┃
                                                                                                   ┃
                                                                                                   ┃
```

![light](match-highlight-overlays.md.snap.1.light.svg)
![dark](match-highlight-overlays.md.snap.1.dark.svg)

Then, move selection to the new-session row so the matched live-session row is
not reversed, making its overlaid span styles visible in the SVG.

    :k M-up
    :snap --color

```terminal
session: onecb                                                                                     ┃
  1/3 | [C-r] repo: none                                                                           ┃
▌  onecb                                                                                           ┃
 ⬤ tone~one                                 c/blue                                                 ┃
                                                                                                   ┃
                                                                                                   ┃
                                                                                                   ┃
                                                                                                   ┃
                                                                                                   ┃
                                                                                                   ┃
```

![light](match-highlight-overlays.md.snap.2.light.svg)
![dark](match-highlight-overlays.md.snap.2.dark.svg)

A second query matches the normally contracted `o` in the repo parent path. The
row should still match, and rendering should expand that parent component enough
to show and highlight the matched `o`.

    :k C-u oneob
    :snap --color

```terminal
session: oneob                                                                                     ┃
  1/3 | [C-r] repo: none | [C-x] close, [C-f] flag                                                 ┃
   oneob                                                                                           ┃
▌⬤ tone~one                                 co/blue                                                ┃
                                                                                                   ┃
                                                                                                   ┃
                                                                                                   ┃
                                                                                                   ┃
                                                                                                   ┃
                                                                                                   ┃
```

![light](match-highlight-overlays.md.snap.3.light.svg)
![dark](match-highlight-overlays.md.snap.3.dark.svg)

